      • authenticateUser

        @POST
 @Path(value="/auth")
public boolean authenticateUser(@QueryParam(value="Email")
                                                              java.lang.String email,
                                                              @QueryParam(value="Pass")
                                                              java.lang.String pass,
                                                              @Session
                                                              javax.servlet.http.HttpSession session)
                                                       throws java.io.IOException
        This is the method that is called when a user has entered their details into the field and attempted to log in.

        When the user logs in successfully, the session they log in with is tagged by setting attributes for the user's email and user_id. The id attribute is used to display all other related information in the application.

        Parameters:
        email - the email address entered by the user
        pass - the unencrypted password entered by the user
        session - the session of the user
        Returns:
        a boolean indicating if the login was successful or not
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException
